TDD exercise complete. Here's a summary:

**Implementation**: `src/game-of-life.ts` - A sparse Game of Life using `Set`/`Map` for neighbor counting (25 lines)

**Tests**: `src/game-of-life.spec.ts` - 9 tests, all passing:
1. Empty grid → empty grid
2. Single cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two adjacent cells die (underpopulation)
4. Cell with 2 neighbors survives
5. Cell with 3 neighbors survives
6. Cell with 4+ neighbors dies (overpopulation)
7. Dead cell with 3 neighbors reproduces
8. Block still life (integration)
9. Blinker oscillator (integration)

**TDD Flow**: The core algorithm was driven by test 4 (survival with 2 neighbors), which required implementing the full neighbor-counting logic. Tests 1-3 were degenerate greens (the initial `return []` satisfied them). Tests 5-9 also passed immediately once the algorithm was in place. One refactoring pass simplified the survival condition from `(isAlive && (count === 2 || count === 3)) || (!isAlive && count === 3)` to the cleaner `count === 3 || (count === 2 && isAlive)`.
